The paper discusses the creation of a decentralized AI cloud through the use of trusted computation and a data market. This falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). Additionally, the paper focuses on machine learning and deep learning applications, which are commonly associated with Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The use of trusted computation also involves security and cryptography, which falls under the category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR). The creation of a data market involves the management and analysis of large datasets, which falls under the category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the creation of a computation market, which involves the allocation of tasks and payments, and falls under the category of Machine Learning (cs.LG).
